While I understand the change of services due to covid and quarantine, I felt that I should share my experience as a potential customer. I am new to the area and googled several places to pick up lunch and A Lot of them are closed OR have different hours that are not updated on google. This one restaurant was, in fact, open so I pulled into an open space in front of the store behind a row of parked cars, but left plenty of room behind me because I noticed that some spots were makred for to-go orders. But I figured since I parked to browse their menu and left their to go lane open, I was fine. While looking online at Their Menu, the manager and a waiter came out to ask if I was waiting for an online order and If Not, I needed to relocate my vehicle Immediately. They did not ask give me an opportunity to explain I was about to order from their establishment and the manager, in particular, spoke over me when I attempted to explain. So I responded that I would just route to a new location and it would be max 5 mins for my gps to load which direction I needed to head to leave there. (Again, I'm new to the area and I am not about to leave a parking spot to find a less threatning parking spot to navigate). She responded "5 mins is not good enough."  And that was the entirety of the exchange. What looked like a promising menu is now on the bottom of my list for potential.  Hope that no one else experiences this same situation here.  Please remember to be considerate of others and stay safe!

When we asked about why we were ignored the bartender began to mock us and talk to other bartenders about us. We proceeded to an outdoor table with our drinks only to be approached by the rude bartender who collected our drinks and asked us to leave.  We had not had any alcohol prior to this and were not starting any trouble. We were a family trying to enjoy a celebratory beer following a happy moment in my daughters life. Apparently they took a dislike to someone questioning their service. I’m sure they deal with a lot of rowdy college kids but we did not fall into this category at all. I am 62 years old and have never in my life been even close to being kicked out of a bar. Needless to say we will not be returning to this establishment. My family will be celebrating our happy moments elsewhere.
